and R14.60/$. Meanwhile gold held onto last week’s gains and was trading at $1 222/oz on Monday morning. Oil was selling for $81.50 a barrel as US/Saudi tensions impact the market, according to TreasuryONE. The currency dealer is keeping its eye on the lira as Turkey on Friday freed an American pastor imprisoned for nearly two years, buying some goodwill from the US. — Fin 24